# Social Features & Mobile Layout Enhancement Plan

This plan outlines the steps to add social interaction (likes, comments, sharing) to reports and sightings, implement a high-quality mobile layout, and add a settings menu.

## Proposed Changes

### Database Schema

#### [NEW] `social_schema.sql`
Create a new SQL file to define the `comments` and `likes` tables and update existing tables.
- `comments` table: [id](file:///c:/Users/Sarvesh/Documents/final_project/Goa%20Eco-Guard/NewFeatures/newFeatures.js#246-253), `user_id`, `item_id`, `item_type` (report/sighting), `text`, `created_at`.
- `likes` table: [id](file:///c:/Users/Sarvesh/Documents/final_project/Goa%20Eco-Guard/NewFeatures/newFeatures.js#246-253), `user_id`, `item_id`, `item_type`.
- Add `likes_count` to `eco_reports` and `eco_sightings`.

### Backend Implementation

#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///c:/Users/Sarvesh/Documents/final_project/Goa%20Eco-Guard/server.js)
- Add endpoints for posting and getting comments.
- Add endpoint for toggling likes.
- Update report/sighting fetch logic to return like/comment counts.

### Frontend Implementation

#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///c:/Users/Sarvesh/Documents/final_project/Goa%20Eco-Guard/index.html)
- Add containers for comments and buttons for likes/sharing in the report cards.
- Add a new "Settings" section/modal.
- Add a mobile bottom navigation bar.

#### [MODIFY] [styles.css](file:///c:/Users/Sarvesh/Documents/final_project/Goa%20Eco-Guard/styles.css)
- Implement glassmorphism styles for a "premium" feel.
- Add styles for the bottom navigation bar.
- Add animations for section transitions.
- Implement dark mode variables.

#### [MODIFY] [script.js](file:///c:/Users/Sarvesh/Documents/final_project/Goa%20Eco-Guard/script.js)
- Implement like/comment/share logic for the main reporting portal.
- Add mobile navigation handling (bottom bar).
- Implement settings logic (theme toggle, etc.).

#### [MODIFY] [NewFeatures/newFeatures.js](file:///c:/Users/Sarvesh/Documents/final_project/Goa%20Eco-Guard/NewFeatures/newFeatures.js)
- Implement like/comment/share logic for the Biodiversity Tracker (sightings).
- Reuse the common social logic if possible.

## Mobile UX Accessibility Enhancements

To solve the issue of the Biodiversity Tracker being hard to reach on mobile, I will implement a "Tabbed Feed" architecture.

### [Component] Navigation & Feed Architecture

#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///c:/Users/Sarvesh/Documents/final_project/Goa%20Eco-Guard/index.html)
- Add a "Sightings" item to the `bottom-nav`.
- Add a new `feed-tabs` container inside the Reporting section for switching between:
  - **Reports** (Pollution reports)
  - **Sightings** (Biodiversity Tracker)
  - **Stories** (Eco-Stories)

#### [MODIFY] [socialStyles.css](file:///c:/Users/Sarvesh/Documents/final_project/Goa%20Eco-Guard/socialStyles.css)
- Create a sticky tab bar style with active indicators (Twitter-like).
- Optimize the bottom nav for 5 items.
- Add smooth transitions when switching tabs and hide overflowing content.

#### [MODIFY] [script.js](file:///c:/Users/Sarvesh/Documents/final_project/Goa%20Eco-Guard/script.js)
- Implement `switchFeed(type)` logic to toggle between reporting, sightings, and stories.
- Handle bottom nav redirection to the specific feed tab.
- **Location Optimization**:
  - Add logic to hide `getLocationBtn` when user starts typing manually.
  - Show "Location found via search" feedback when manual typing geocodes successfully.

#### [MODIFY] [socialStyles.css](file:///c:/Users/Sarvesh/Documents/final_project/Goa%20Eco-Guard/socialStyles.css)
- Implement media queries for responsive navigation (Mobile vs Desktop).
- Add styles for location feedback status (e.g., `.location-found`).

#### [MODIFY] [NewFeatures/newFeatures.js](file:///c:/Users/Sarvesh/Documents/final_project/Goa%20Eco-Guard/NewFeatures/newFeatures.js)
- Implement `searchSightingLocation` to geocode manual input in the Biodiversity Tracker.
- Allow form submission if coordinates are found via manual typing (removing the hard requirement to click "Use Current Location").
- Hide `nfGetSightLocation` button when user scales manual input.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- **Bottom Nav**: Click "Sightings", verify it scrolls to the feed and selects the "Sightings" tab.
- **Tab Switching**: Tap "Reports" -> "Sightings" -> "Stories", verify content updates instantly without full page scroll.
- **Stickiness**: Scroll down the feed and ensure the tabs stay at the top of the mobile viewport.

